Deposit(address,address,uint256).details: Function wrapper around the _Deposit event so that it can be used by contracts.  Can be used to log a deposit to an account.

params._from: The address that deposited the funds.
params.accountAddress: The address of the account the funds were added to.
params.value: The amount that was added to the account.

InsufficientFunds(address,uint256,uint25.details: Function wrapper around the _InsufficientFunds event so that it can be used by contracts.  Can be used to log a failed withdrawl from an account.

params.accountAddress: The address of the account the funds were to be withdrawn from.
params.balance: The current balance of the account.
params.value: The amount that was attempted to be withdrawn from the account.

Withdrawal(address,uint256).details: Function wrapper around the _Withdrawal event so that it can be used by contracts.  Can be used to log a withdrawl from an account.

params.accountAddress: The address of the account the funds were withdrawn from.
params.value: The amount that was withdrawn to the account.

addFunds(AccountingLib.Bank storage,addr.details: Low level method for adding funds to an account.  Protects against overflow.

params.accountAddress: The address of the account the funds should be added to.
params.self: The Bank instance to operate on.
params.value: The amount that should be added to the account.

deductFunds(AccountingLib.Bank storage,a.details: Low level method for removing funds from an account.  Protects against underflow.

params.accountAddress: The address of the account the funds should be deducted from.
params.self: The Bank instance to operate on.
params.value: The amount that should be deducted from the account.

deposit(AccountingLib.Bank storage,addre.details: Safe function for depositing funds.  Returns boolean for whether the deposit was successful

params.accountAddress: The address of the account the funds should be added to.
params.self: The Bank instance to operate on.
params.value: The amount that should be added to the account.

withdraw(AccountingLib.Bank storage,addr.details: Safe function for withdrawing funds.  Returns boolean for whether the deposit was successful as well as sending the amount in ether to the account address.

params.accountAddress: The address of the account the funds should be withdrawn from.
params.self: The Bank instance to operate on.
params.value: The amount that should be withdrawn from the account.

exists(GroveLib.Index storage,bytes32).details: Checks whether a node for the given unique identifier exists within the given index.

params.id: The unique identifier of the data element to check for.
params.index: The index that should be searched

getNextNode(GroveLib.Index storage,bytes.details: Retrieve the node id of the previous node in the tree.

params.id: The id for the node to be looked up.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.

getNodeHeight(GroveLib.Index storage,byt.details: Retrieve the height of the node.

params.id: The id for the node to be looked up.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.

getNodeId(GroveLib.Index storage,bytes32.details: Retrieve the unique identifier for the node.

params.id: The id for the node to be looked up.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.

getNodeLeftChild(GroveLib.Index storage,.details: Retrieve the left child id of the node.

params.id: The id for the node to be looked up.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.

getNodeParent(GroveLib.Index storage,byt.details: Retrieve the parent id of the node.

params.id: The id for the node to be looked up.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.

getNodeRightChild(GroveLib.Index storage.details: Retrieve the right child id of the node.

params.id: The id for the node to be looked up.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.

getNodeValue(GroveLib.Index storage,byte.details: Retrieve the value for the node.

params.id: The id for the node to be looked up.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.

getPreviousNode(GroveLib.Index storage,b.details: Retrieve the node id of the next node in the tree.

params.id: The id for the node to be looked up.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.

insert(GroveLib.Index storage,bytes32,in.details: Updates or Inserts the id into the index at its appropriate location based on the value provided.

params.id: The unique identifier of the data element the index node will represent.
params.index: The index that the node is part of.
params.value: The value of the data element that represents it's total ordering with respect to other elementes.

params.operator: One of '>', '>=', '<', '<=', '==' to specify what type of comparison operator should be used.

remove(GroveLib.Index storage,bytes32).details: Remove the node for the given unique identifier from the index.

params.id: The unique identifier of the data element to remove.
params.index: The index that should be removed

AddedToGeneration(address,uint256).details: Function to expose the _AddedToGeneration event to contracts.

RemovedFromGeneration(address,uint256).details: Function to expose the _AddedToGeneration event to contracts.

addToBond(ResourcePoolLib.Pool storage,a.details: Adds the amount to an account's bond balance.

canEnterPool(ResourcePoolLib.Pool storag.details: Returns a boolean as to whether the provided address is allowed to enter the pool at this time.

params.minimumBond: The minimum bond amount that should be required for entry.

canExitPool(ResourcePoolLib.Pool storage.details: Returns a boolean as to whether the provided address is allowed to exit the pool at this time.

createNextGeneration(ResourcePoolLib.Poo.details: Creates the next generation for the given pool.  All members from the current generation are carried over (with their order randomized).  The current generation will have it's endAt block set.

deductFromBond(ResourcePoolLib.Pool stor.details: Subtracts the amount from an account's bond balance.

enterPool(ResourcePoolLib.Pool storage,a.details: Adds the address to pool by adding them to the next generation (as well as creating it if it doesn't exist).

params.minimumBond: The minimum bond amount that should be required for entry.
params.resourceAddress: The address to be added to the pool

exitPool(ResourcePoolLib.Pool storage,ad.details: Removes the address from the pool by removing them from the next generation (as well as creating it if it doesn't exist)

getCurrentGenerationId(ResourcePoolLib.P.details: Returns the first generation that is currently active.

getGenerationForWindow(ResourcePoolLib.P.details: Returns the first generation id that fully contains the block window provided.

params.leftBound: The left bound for the block window (inclusive)
params.rightBound: The right bound for the block window (inclusive)

getNextGenerationId(ResourcePoolLib.Pool.details: Returns the first generation in the future that has not yet started.

isInCurrentGeneration(ResourcePoolLib.Po.details: Returns a boolean for whether the given address is in the current generation.

params.resourceAddress: The address to check membership of

isInGeneration(ResourcePoolLib.Pool stor.details: Returns a boolean for whether the given address is in the given generation.

params.generationId: The id of the generation to check.
params.resourceAddress: The address to check membership of

isInNextGeneration(ResourcePoolLib.Pool.details: Returns a boolean for whether the given address is in the next queued generation.

params.resourceAddress: The address to check membership of

isInPool(ResourcePoolLib.Pool storage,ad.details: Returns a boolean for whether the given address is in either the current generation or the next queued generation.

params.resourceAddress: The address to check membership of

removeFromGeneration(ResourcePoolLib.Poo.details: Removes the address from a generation's members array. Returns boolean as to whether removal was successful.

params.generationId: The id of the generation to operate on.

withdrawBond(ResourcePoolLib.Pool storag.details: Withdraws a bond amount from an address's bond account, sending them the corresponding amount in ether.

bytesToUInt(bytes32).details: Converts a numeric string to it's unsigned integer representation.

uintToBytes(uint256).details: Converts an unsigned integert to its string representation.
